  "title": "Operations Associate (US Shift)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your new company</strong> </p><p>A leading hedge fund with a presence in Asia and Middle East. </p><p><strong>Your new role</strong> </p><p>As an Operations Associate, you will be responsible for </p><ul><li>Execute and settle trades in Fixed Income and Equity markets, ensuring smooth transaction processing.</li><li>Perform timely reconciliation of positions and cash balances across internal systems, custodians, and counterparties.</li><li>Collaborate with front office teams and external partners to investigate and resolve trade discrepancies.</li><li>Monitor operational risks and support process improvements to strengthen trade settlement efficiency.</li></ul><p><strong>What you'll need to succeed</strong> </p><ul><li>Possess a minimum of 3 years’ experience in Middle-Back Office functions within Financial Services, with a focus on Fixed Income and Equity.</li><li>Adept at handling trade settlement, reconciliation, and discrepancy resolution across internal systems and external counterparties.</li><li>Flexible and comfortable working US shift hours (9pm–6am) to support global operations.</li><li>Demonstrate ambition, resilience, and a strong drive to succeed in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul><p><strong>What you'll get in return</strong> </p><ul><li>Opportunity to collaborate with a global team, gaining exposure to diverse markets and practices.</li><li>Experience within a leading hedge fund environment, offering insight into investment strategies.</li><li>Accelerated learning curve, with hands-on involvement in complex trade processes and operational improvements.</li></ul><p></p>",
